 ## Failure taxonomy
 
 Failures fall into several categories:
 
-- **Structure drift:** Breaking or changing the prescribed section order, headings, or file names.
-- **Content sprawl:** Mixing multiple job types (rules, evidence, narrative) within one chunk or file.
-- **Label ambiguity:** Using inconsistent or missing labels, leading to poor retrieval.
-- **Destructive rewrite:** Replacing entire sections instead of patching specific spans.
-- **Authority blur:** Failing to declare which source governs a file or chunk.
-- **Hidden gaps:** Hiding unresolved questions or treating provisional content as authoritative.
